# Planner Standards

## Arabic-First
- Arabic is primary design language. RTL implications at requirement level.
- No feature approved without RTL feasibility assessment.

## Cultural UX
- RTL eye-tracking (right → left hierarchy). Information density for Arabic.
- Icons, colors, imagery culturally appropriate for MENA.

## Documentation
- PRDs include RTL & localization sections.
- Terminology aligned with backend context tables and APIs.
- Professional Arabic for user-facing content. No literal English→Arabic.

## Cultural Fit Audit
- Language tone, numeric formats, dates (Hijri/Gregorian).
- Error and empty states respectful and clear.
